title._content: Break through of old platforms for opening of the new Sydney Railway Station (NSW)

description._content: Title: Break through of old platforms for opening of the new Sydney Railway Station (NSW) Dated: c. 31/12/1906 Digital ID: 17420_a014_a0140000262 Rights: No known copyright restrictions www.records.nsw.gov.au/about-us/rights-and-permissions We'd love to hear from you if you use our photos/documents. Many other photos in our collection are available to view and browse on our website using Photo Investigator.

note._content: There is a significant access/ baggage tunnel system under here feeding each platform hence the louvre window staircase on the right. The drainage grate between the tracks still exists and probably fed a pipe much deeper than the tunnels.
